headline: Is Morgan Stanley’s Downgrade and 2025 Earnings Cut Altering The Investment Case For Archer-Daniels-Midland (ADM)?
summary: Morgan Stanley recently downgraded Archer-Daniels-Midland (ADM) to Underweight, pointing to regulatory delays, weaker margins in its Carbohydrate Solutions unit, and a reduced 2025 profit outlook amid US biofuel policy uncertainty and global trade disruptions. This marks ADM’s third consecutive cut to its 2025 earnings guidance and its weakest projected earnings since 2019, highlighting how policy and margin pressures are weighing on one of the world’s largest agricultural processors.
